  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis:

      Stimulation of the SPG at low frequencies (20 Hz)is believed to cause a physiological
      parasympathetic upregulation which increases mean velocity in middle cerebral artery (VMCA)
      and diameter of the superficial temporal artery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
